WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:04.502
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Tradition at the Crab Shack was...</i>

00:04.604 --> 00:08.301
<i>if you passed out the week before Christmas,</i>
<i>you got decorated.</i>

00:08.408 --> 00:12.777
<i>I wanted tojoin in, but there were certain times</i>
<i>when I needed to be lookin'after Randy-</i>

00:12.879 --> 00:14.972
- <i>like when he was readin'the comics.</i>
- [Laughing]

00:15.081 --> 00:17.345
Oh, God. That's terrible.

00:17.450 --> 00:19.850
- [Laughing]
- <i>## [Jukebox: Country Christmas]</i>

00:19.953 --> 00:21.853
That's not funny at all.

00:21.955 --> 00:24.014
Randy, remember,
comics are only on the left.

00:24.124 --> 00:27.184
If you keep readin', you'll run
onto the side with the obituaries.

00:27.293 --> 00:29.784
- So what do we do?
- Fold the paper.

00:29.896 --> 00:31.796
Thanks, Earl.

00:31.898 --> 00:33.798
<i>[Crowd]</i>
<i>Three, two, one!</i>

00:33.900 --> 00:37.199
- [Electricity Crackles]
- [Cheering, Laughing]

00:37.303 --> 00:40.431
<i>People, what have I told you?</i>
<i>If you're going to decorate the drunks...</i>

00:40.540 --> 00:43.634
<i>please have a fire extinguisher</i>
<i>standing by.</i>

00:45.078 --> 00:47.638
<i>My name is Earl.</i>

00:54.120 --> 00:56.452
Uh, excuse me.
My wife and I were just driving home...

00:56.556 --> 00:59.992
from building Nerf playgrounds
for autistic children, and, uh, we ran out of gas.

01:00.093 --> 01:02.084
She would've come with me,
but she's shy...

01:02.195 --> 01:04.254
because we had to sell her hair
for baby formula.

01:04.364 --> 01:07.094
If you'd loan me a 20,
I'll, uh, mail it back to you.

01:07.200 --> 01:10.169
Goodness me.
That is such a sad story.

01:10.270 --> 01:12.465
And there were so many details,
it has to be true.

01:12.572 --> 01:14.972
Would you mind sharing it
with my friends inside?

01:15.075 --> 01:17.805
I'm sure they'd love to help.

01:17.911 --> 01:20.379
[All Laughing]

01:21.915 --> 01:25.146
And then he said he had a bald wife
who sold her hair for-

01:25.251 --> 01:27.219
What was it she sold it for?

01:27.320 --> 01:29.311
Baby formula.

01:29.422 --> 01:32.858
[Laughing]

01:32.959 --> 01:35.587
[Laughing]
What an idiot.

01:35.695 --> 01:38.163
The baby formula is "man plus woman."

01:38.264 --> 01:40.960
Everybody knows that.

01:41.067 --> 01:44.525
<i>[Earl Narrating] That hustler comin'in here</i>
<i>reminded me of number 201 on my list-</i>

01:44.637 --> 01:47.037
<i>conned an old man</i>
<i>out of a hundred bucks.</i>

01:47.140 --> 01:51.338
<i>A couple weeks before I discovered karma,</i>
<i>me and Joy were watching TV.</i>

01:51.444 --> 01:53.435
[Male Announcer]
There are one million orphans in Africa.

01:53.546 --> 01:56.947
These children do not ask,
"What shall I eat for dinner?"

01:57.050 --> 01:59.541
<i>They ask, "Will I ever eat again?"</i>

01:59.652 --> 02:02.712
Change the channel.
I can't eat while I'm lookin' at that kid.

02:02.822 --> 02:04.790
I'll try, but my hands are saucy.

02:04.891 --> 02:08.952
<i>For pennies a day, you can make sure</i>
<i>little Kwame has rice and broth to eat...</i>

02:09.062 --> 02:12.122
instead of bowl after bowl of mud.

02:12.232 --> 02:16.100
Those kids really pull
at your heartstrings.

02:16.202 --> 02:19.296
- Makes you think, doesn't it?
- [Sucks Teeth] Yep.

02:19.405 --> 02:22.670
We can make a fortune
off those scrawny little tearjerkers.

02:22.775 --> 02:25.869
- [Laughing]
- You got rib meat in your teeth.

02:25.979 --> 02:28.504
Well, get it.

02:28.615 --> 02:31.140
Man, that's really in there.

02:38.124 --> 02:42.857
Is this true?
Nine out of 10 African children die every minute?

02:42.962 --> 02:44.987
Africa's hard on kids...

02:45.098 --> 02:47.965
what with the hot sun
and giant leeches...

02:48.067 --> 02:51.002
and no... speed limits.

02:51.104 --> 02:53.902
- <i>Suppose you want some cash.</i>
- Oh, no, no, no.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.907
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>The first rule of scammin'money out of people...</i>

02:56.009 --> 02:57.909
<i>is to look like</i>
<i>you</i> aren't <i>lookin'for money.</i>

02:58.011 --> 02:59.911
We're not askin' for money.

03:00.013 --> 03:02.277
But if you have trouble
sleepin' tonight...

03:02.382 --> 03:04.782
you can just send a check
to the address on the back.

03:04.884 --> 03:08.513
<i>The second rule of scammin'</i>
<i>was not to tell Randy it was a scam.</i>

03:08.621 --> 03:11.715
<i>'Cause there's no better salesman than</i>
<i>someone who believes he's tellin'the truth.</i>

03:11.824 --> 03:13.724
All they're eatin' is air.

03:13.826 --> 03:15.794
And the orphans' bellies
are really big...

03:15.895 --> 03:17.795
but it turns out
they're totally empty.

03:17.897 --> 03:20.923
And all they're askin' for
is a cup of coffee a day.

03:21.034 --> 03:23.025
Oh, my God!
Nine more just died.

03:23.136 --> 03:25.661
Open your eyes, people.
Take a pamphlet.

03:25.772 --> 03:27.865
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>We handed out a hundred pamphlets...</i>

03:27.974 --> 03:29.874
<i>and even went down</i>
<i>and got a "po"box...</i>

03:29.976 --> 03:31.967
<i>so the address</i>
<i>would look more official.</i>

03:32.078 --> 03:35.514
<i>Most people saw through our scam,</i>
<i>but we did get one bite.</i>

03:35.615 --> 03:37.981
Ka-ching! It worked!

03:38.084 --> 03:41.451
Some guy in Nathanville sent us
a hundred-dollar check for the orphans.

03:41.554 --> 03:46.082
- Sweet.
- Why are <i>you</i> gettin' the money
for the African orphans?

03:49.095 --> 03:51.563
Randy, maybe it's time to tell you.

03:51.664 --> 03:54.189
This was a scam.

03:54.300 --> 03:56.291
It was?

03:56.402 --> 03:58.302
You always get me.

03:58.404 --> 04:01.134
[Laughing]
Oh, man. I cried so much.

04:01.241 --> 04:03.971
<i>I didn't even tell you about</i>
<i>the nightmares I've been havin'.</i>

04:04.077 --> 04:06.637
Whew. Wow.
What a relief.

04:06.746 --> 04:09.078
So there's no starvin' children
in Africa then?

04:11.651 --> 04:13.016
No.

04:13.119 --> 04:15.553
<i>[Earl Narrating] And so me and Randy</i>
<i>went to find the guy...</i>

04:15.655 --> 04:18.021
<i>who'd sent us that check</i>
<i>all those years ago.</i>

04:21.861 --> 04:24.887
Did you know Aunt Ramona
wrote a book about barbecue sauces?

04:24.998 --> 04:26.898
Mom says it bought her a condo.

04:27.000 --> 04:31.198
I think I'm gonna write a book about
barbecue sauces. Maybe other sauces too.

04:31.304 --> 04:33.329
Randy, you don't know
anything about sauce.

04:33.439 --> 04:35.464
People write books
about things they know.

04:35.575 --> 04:37.873
Think about how much meat
Aunt Ramona eats.

04:37.977 --> 04:41.071
Maybe I could write a book
about how things taste-

04:41.180 --> 04:43.205
- you know, nonfood things.
- [Doorbell Rings]

04:43.316 --> 04:45.284
I have a curious tongue.

04:45.385 --> 04:48.616
- That could be the name of the book.
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>

04:48.721 --> 04:51.053
- Mr. Hill?
- Yes?

04:51.157 --> 04:53.682
I don't know if you remember,
but three years ago...

04:53.793 --> 04:56.853
you sent me a hundred dollars
to help save an orphan kid in Africa.

04:56.963 --> 04:59.796
Of course. Mbungo.

04:59.899 --> 05:03.630
[Chuckling]
That little fella. Why, he's changed my life.

05:03.736 --> 05:05.328
'Scuse me?

05:05.438 --> 05:08.566
- <i>## ["Here Comes Santa Claus"]</i>
- Here are some drawings Mbungo made me.

05:08.675 --> 05:10.575
All his letters...

05:10.677 --> 05:13.612
and his report cards
from the village school.

05:13.713 --> 05:15.613
Teacher comments:

05:15.715 --> 05:18.878
"Plays well with zebras.
Expert stick-thrower."

05:18.985 --> 05:21.545
You can tell he's special.

05:21.654 --> 05:25.988
- So you been sendin' checks this whole time?
- A hundred dollars a month.

05:26.092 --> 05:30.392
But it's worth it.
Take a look at this kid.

05:30.496 --> 05:34.364
<i>Knowin'that I make a difference</i>
<i>in Mbungo's life...</i>

05:34.467 --> 05:36.435
it makes me feel-

05:38.604 --> 05:41.232
- Joy.
- Exactly.

05:41.341 --> 05:43.434
- Joy.
- <i>[Randy] Ow!</i>

05:43.543 --> 05:45.875
Oh!

05:47.814 --> 05:51.841
Cactus: Painful, but worth it.

05:56.956 --> 05:58.981
Come on, Darnell.
Let me lick your head.

05:59.092 --> 06:03.188
It'll be in my new book-
right after "all ofJoy and Darnell's spoons."

06:03.296 --> 06:05.594
I guess,
if it's for research purposes.

06:05.698 --> 06:08.098
You been scammin' that poor man
for three years?

06:08.201 --> 06:10.101
I can't believe you're not
ashamed of yourself.

06:10.203 --> 06:13.036
If I had only fooled him once,
it'd be shame on me.

06:13.139 --> 06:16.131
But I have fooled him a bunch of times,
so, duh, it's shame on him.

06:16.242 --> 06:18.142
It's cruel, Joy.

06:18.244 --> 06:21.270
You didn't just con him out of
thousands of dollars. He loves that kid.

06:21.381 --> 06:24.282
How's he gonna feel if he finds out
Mbungo doesn't even exist?

06:24.384 --> 06:26.284
Well, you better not
tell him the truth...

06:26.386 --> 06:29.048
'cause you'll ruin Christmas
for a lot of people in this trailer park.

06:29.155 --> 06:31.055
What?

06:31.157 --> 06:34.422
<i>[Earl Narrating] Turns outJoy was so proud</i>
<i>ofkeeping the African orphan scheme going...</i>

06:34.527 --> 06:37.087
<i>she couldn't resist bragging</i>
<i>to her friends in the trailer park.</i>

06:37.196 --> 06:42.065
<i>Her friend Sylvia used some barbecue ashes</i>
<i>to fake a disaster photo.</i>

06:42.168 --> 06:44.898
[Sobbing]

06:45.004 --> 06:48.667
<i>Then she sent Mr. Hill</i>
<i>a letter asking for donations...</i>

06:48.775 --> 06:51.300
<i>for families who lost</i>
<i>their homes in wildfires.</i>

06:52.612 --> 06:54.580
<i>Tammy went the other way.</i>

06:59.452 --> 07:01.420
<i>She sent Mr. Hill a letter</i>
<i>asking for donations...</i>

07:01.521 --> 07:04.149
<i>for families displaced by floods.</i>

07:04.257 --> 07:07.249
<i>And pretty soon, he was</i>
<i>sending monthly checks to everybody.</i>

07:07.360 --> 07:10.158
- <i>This is wrong, Joy, and you know it.</i>
- Says you.

07:10.263 --> 07:13.232
Sure I took from one person,
but I gave the idea to two other people...

07:13.332 --> 07:15.800
which means I have given
twice as much as I have taken.

07:15.902 --> 07:18.097
So suck on that.

07:22.775 --> 07:25.642
Hair: Tastes like marijuana.

07:29.515 --> 07:32.416
Joy's not gonna
budge on this, Randy.

07:32.518 --> 07:35.316
I don't want to, but maybe
I should just write Mr. Hill a check...

07:35.421 --> 07:37.821
for all the moneyJoy and her friends
conned him out of.

07:37.924 --> 07:40.222
[Groans]
Snoopy tastes horrible.

07:40.326 --> 07:44.160
I think writing a check is the only way
I can cross Mr. Hill off my list.

07:44.263 --> 07:46.823
<i>Oh, God. That's terrible.</i>

07:46.933 --> 07:49.299
Randy, just fold the paper over, okay?

07:53.406 --> 07:56.341
<i>Well, I hope you're happy.</i>

07:56.442 --> 08:00.902
Oh, my God! Mr. Hill had a stroke and died?
This is horrible.

08:01.013 --> 08:04.176
I just took a close-up picture of EarlJunior
with flies in the corner of his eyes.

08:04.283 --> 08:07.810
Do you know how hard it is to get a kid
and a fly to hold still for a picture?

08:07.920 --> 08:09.751
Read the rest of the obituary.

08:09.856 --> 08:14.054
"Mr. Hill is leaving everything
to his three favorite charities:

08:14.160 --> 08:18.028
"Pimmit Hills African Relief,
Pimmit Hills Wildfire Victims...

08:18.130 --> 08:21.099
and Pimmit Hills Flood Helpers
Give Us Money Fund."

08:21.200 --> 08:24.727
Darnell! Mbungo's sugar daddy
just took a dirt nap, and we're rich!

08:24.837 --> 08:26.771
Not if I have anything to say about it.

08:26.873 --> 08:29.239
<i>I'm gonna cross</i>
<i>Mr. Hill off my list...</i>

08:29.342 --> 08:32.277
by making sure you and your friends
never get that money.

08:32.378 --> 08:35.677
That's my money, Earl Hickey. Don't you
mess with me. You know what I'm capable of.

08:35.781 --> 08:37.908
You know why you only got nine toes.

08:38.017 --> 08:41.418
<i>[Earl Narrating] So me and Randy</i>
<i>headed over to Mr. Hill's house.</i>

08:41.521 --> 08:45.753
This'll be just like old times-
breaking into a house.

08:45.858 --> 08:48.292
You think we can steal
a few things too?

08:48.394 --> 08:50.988
I brought a grocery list
of stuff we're out of.

08:51.097 --> 08:53.224
Deodorant, Fig Newtons, underwear.

08:53.332 --> 08:55.232
Randy, we're not taking anything.

08:55.334 --> 08:57.928
We just have to find something
with Mr. Hill's lawyer's name on it...

08:58.037 --> 09:00.631
so we can tell the lawyer
those charities are fake.

09:02.875 --> 09:05.742
I knew it. That bastard's trying
to screw up our inheritance.

09:12.852 --> 09:14.752
Oh, my God. This is it.

09:14.854 --> 09:16.913
It's his will.

09:17.023 --> 09:21.016
"Charities shall receive monies
in the amount of $280,000."

09:21.127 --> 09:23.152
[Gasps]

09:25.731 --> 09:27.995
The lawyer's name and address
are right here.

09:31.470 --> 09:35.270
They found the will.
That old coot was holding on to $280,000.

09:35.374 --> 09:38.207
Bling! I'm gonna buy a fur coat
with the little head still on it...

09:38.311 --> 09:41.906
so people will stare and I'll be all,
"Yeah, this bitch is real."

09:42.014 --> 09:44.915
Yeah! Get down.
They're comin' out.

09:50.089 --> 09:54.355
We gotta get that will away from 'em.
We'll just keep following 'em real quiet.

09:56.796 --> 09:59.526
- [Engine Starts]
- ## [Stereo: Loud Rock]

09:59.632 --> 10:04.535
It's Joy. She must've figured out
we have the will. We gotta split up.

10:04.637 --> 10:07.197
You take the will and start walking
to the lawyer's office.

10:07.306 --> 10:10.366
Joy will be sure I kept it,
and she'll follow me.

10:10.476 --> 10:13.536
- [Mouthing Words]
- What are you doin'?

10:13.646 --> 10:17.309
I'm pretendin' I'm mad at you,
and that's why I'm gettin' out of the car.

10:22.521 --> 10:24.421
What do you mean you hate our troops?

10:24.523 --> 10:26.423
They're protecting our freedom!

10:26.525 --> 10:29.892
- I'm gettin' outta your car!
- [Door Slams]

10:41.941 --> 10:44.136
- [Gasps]
- Hand me the will, dummy.

10:44.243 --> 10:47.303
Uh, maybe you should
give <i>me</i> the will.

10:47.413 --> 10:51.042
- I don't have the will.
- Well, I do.

10:51.150 --> 10:54.551
Not. Not. Not.
Not. Not.

10:54.654 --> 10:57.384
Not. Not. Not. Not.

11:00.493 --> 11:03.462
Hello. We're here to pick up our checks
from the dead guy.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.825
You are Mr. Fischer, the lawyer,
aren't you?

11:06.932 --> 11:10.993
<i>Yes, I'm Mr. Fischer,</i>
<i>and I believe you know Mr. Hickey.</i>

11:14.006 --> 11:16.839
- Son of a bitch.
- Hello, Joy.

11:16.942 --> 11:18.842
I knew you'd follow Randy.

11:18.944 --> 11:23.108
<i>That gave mejust enough time to get here</i>
<i>and tell Mr. Fischer everything.</i>

11:23.215 --> 11:25.115
Thank you, Mr. Hickey.

11:25.217 --> 11:27.913
You can cross Mr. Hill
off your list.

11:28.020 --> 11:29.749
See ya around, Joy.

11:32.725 --> 11:35.285
You had to stop for tacos.

11:35.394 --> 11:37.294
Uh, counteroffer?

11:39.365 --> 11:41.265
'Scuse me?

11:41.367 --> 11:46.134
I could... do a little paperwork magic
and make your charities legal.

11:46.238 --> 11:48.138
Then you could collect the cash.

11:49.909 --> 11:51.809
And what's your kickback?

11:51.911 --> 11:53.811
Oh, I don't need any money.

11:53.913 --> 11:57.974
It's just that...
I'm a very lonely man.

11:58.084 --> 12:00.814
My wife's dead- to me.

12:00.920 --> 12:02.820
She lives in Oregon now
with the kids.

12:02.922 --> 12:05.356
I'm not supposed to know that,
but the cops have slipped up.

12:05.458 --> 12:07.449
<i>I see where you're goin'with this.</i>

12:07.560 --> 12:11.121
You'll help us out with the documents
as long as you get to have sex with Sylvia here.

12:11.230 --> 12:14.563
Shut up, Sylvia. That's a lot of money,
and you are not married.

12:14.667 --> 12:18.660
Well, actually, what I had in mind
was something in a blonde.

12:18.771 --> 12:21.535
- Oh, I don't have-
- Come on, Joy. That's a lot of money.

12:21.640 --> 12:23.335
Zip it!

12:24.376 --> 12:26.571
Blonde's not on the menu.

12:26.679 --> 12:29.807
How about we give you
Sylvia and $6,000?

12:29.915 --> 12:33.282
- Or Tammy and 3,500.
- Can you go to five on Tammy?

12:33.385 --> 12:35.319
- I don't know if I'm down with sleepin' with-
- Deal.

12:36.722 --> 12:41.091
<i>[Scoffs]</i>
<i>For cryin'out loud.</i>

12:41.260 --> 12:43.319
[Table Shaking]

12:46.499 --> 12:49.662
<i>[Earl Narrating] While Tammy and Mr. Fischer</i>
<i>were getting busy under his desk...</i>

12:49.769 --> 12:52.704
<i>Joy and Sylvia were busy</i>
<i>getting the $5,000 in bribe money...</i>

12:52.805 --> 12:54.705
<i>from a local loan shark.</i>

12:54.807 --> 12:58.140
- Five grand.
- Thank you very much.

12:58.244 --> 12:59.939
Here's a check for you.

13:00.045 --> 13:03.503
And one for you.
And one for you.

13:03.616 --> 13:05.379
Pleasure doin' business with you.

13:05.484 --> 13:09.420
[Chortling]
Ah! Yeah!

13:09.522 --> 13:11.513
[Phone Beeping]

13:11.624 --> 13:13.649
- [Line Clicks]
- It worked.

13:13.759 --> 13:16.523
- You got all the money?
- Every penny.

13:16.629 --> 13:19.598
- What are you gonna do now?
- I'm gonna take it back where it belongs.

13:19.698 --> 13:22.633
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Which was to Mr. Hill, who wasn't really dead.</i>

13:22.735 --> 13:24.862
<i>You see, I'djust pulled a huge scam.</i>

13:24.970 --> 13:28.633
<i>First, I got Mr. Hill</i>
<i>out of town for a few days...</i>

13:28.741 --> 13:32.802
<i>by arranging for him to win a vacation</i>
<i>to the national rodeo championships.</i>

13:32.912 --> 13:35.312
Yahoo!

13:35.414 --> 13:37.848
<i>And the old scam rules still applied.</i>

13:37.950 --> 13:41.886
<i>I knew the best way to convinceJoy it was real</i>
<i>was to make Randy think it was real.</i>

13:41.987 --> 13:44.353
Oh, God. That's terrible.

13:46.525 --> 13:49.653
<i>I also knew hearin'about all that money</i>
<i>would makeJoy greedy.</i>

13:49.762 --> 13:52.925
Darnell! Mbungo's sugar daddy
just took a dirt nap, and we're rich!

13:53.032 --> 13:55.023
<i>I knewJoy wouldn't</i>
<i>let me out ofher sight...</i>

13:55.134 --> 13:58.262
<i>but before we broke into the house,</i>
<i>I had to make sure she'd follow me there.</i>

14:00.206 --> 14:04.006
<i>Then I just had to pretend to find</i>
<i>the will I'd planted in Mr. Hill's house.</i>

14:04.109 --> 14:06.441
<i>Oh, my God.</i>
<i>This is it. It's his will.</i>

14:07.880 --> 14:10.974
<i>I needed to makeJoy think</i>
<i>she was a step ahead of me...</i>

14:11.083 --> 14:13.074
<i>so I gave the fake will to Randy...</i>

14:13.185 --> 14:15.244
<i>knowing she'd get it away from him.</i>

14:15.354 --> 14:18.221
<i>But to actually get these marks</i>
<i>to hand over the money...</i>

14:18.324 --> 14:20.952
<i>I needed someone</i>
<i>to gain their confidence-</i>

14:21.060 --> 14:22.960
<i>somebody willing to scam people...</i>

14:23.062 --> 14:25.223
<i>who also had a grudge againstJoy.</i>

14:25.331 --> 14:29.427
<i>And of course, my first rule</i>
<i>of getting money out of people still applied-</i>

14:29.535 --> 14:31.696
<i>look like you're not</i>
<i>lookin'for money.</i>

14:31.804 --> 14:36.434
Well, actually, what I had in mind
was something in a blonde.

14:36.542 --> 14:38.442
<i>And after I knew we had the money...</i>

14:38.544 --> 14:41.274
<i>there was only one thing</i>
<i>left to take care of.</i>

14:41.380 --> 14:43.280
I'm gonna take it back
where it belongs.

14:43.382 --> 14:46.749
Mr. Hill gets back from
the rodeo championships next week.

14:46.852 --> 14:48.820
I think he's gonna be very happy.

14:51.056 --> 14:54.583
I'm sorry, Earl,
but I letJoy get the will.

14:54.693 --> 14:58.754
That was my plan, Randy.
This whole thing was a scam.

14:59.932 --> 15:02.423
[Laughing]
Oh, man, Earl!

15:02.534 --> 15:04.764
<i>You got me again.</i>

15:04.870 --> 15:06.861
Wow. This was a long one though.

15:06.972 --> 15:09.133
All that runnin' around, karma.

15:09.241 --> 15:12.642
I believed in that crazy list
for three years.

15:12.745 --> 15:15.509
[Laughing]
Bravo, Earl. Bravo.

15:17.349 --> 15:20.182
<i>[Earl Narrating] And when Mr. Hill</i>
<i>got back from his vacation...</i>

15:20.286 --> 15:23.016
<i>I was there waitin'</i>
<i>to tell him the whole story-</i>

15:23.122 --> 15:27.081
<i>from my original scam all the way up</i>
<i>to gettin'his money back from Joy.</i>

15:28.827 --> 15:32.092
This money covers every nickel
Joy and her friends conned you out of...

15:32.197 --> 15:35.655
<i>plus another hundred</i>
<i>for breaking your front door lock.</i>

15:35.768 --> 15:38.032
And I think Randy took
some of your underwear.

15:38.137 --> 15:40.264
I can't believe it.

15:40.372 --> 15:43.603
There were no hurricanes, no fires?

15:43.709 --> 15:45.802
No Mbungos?

15:48.747 --> 15:50.715
I'm such an idiot.

15:50.816 --> 15:52.716
But-Wait.

15:52.818 --> 15:55.218
The important thing is
you got your money back now.

15:55.321 --> 15:58.222
Well, how's that supposed
to make me feel better?

15:58.324 --> 16:02.385
I'm still the moron who thought
he bought an entire African village...

16:02.494 --> 16:04.394
athlete's foot vaccinations.

16:05.664 --> 16:07.564
You know what you need?

16:07.666 --> 16:10.032
Let's go laugh in their faces.
It'll feel great.

16:12.404 --> 16:14.304
<i>I took Mr. Hill to the trailer park...</i>

16:14.406 --> 16:17.000
<i>so we could laugh at the people</i>
<i>we'd gotten revenge on.</i>

16:17.109 --> 16:19.509
<i>I had hoped that the opportunity</i>
<i>to do a victory dance...</i>

16:19.611 --> 16:23.479
<i>in front of the lowlives who had been</i>
<i>rippin'him off would cheer him right up.</i>

16:23.582 --> 16:27.211
<i>[Water Running]</i>

16:27.319 --> 16:30.311
<i>But when we got there,</i>
<i>things had changed.</i>

16:30.422 --> 16:33.118
<i>What was once</i>
<i>a middle-to-low-end trailer park...</i>

16:33.225 --> 16:36.058
<i>now looked like</i>
<i>a third world country.</i>

16:38.263 --> 16:39.890
[Flies Buzzing]

16:41.667 --> 16:44.033
Joy, what happened to all of you?

16:44.136 --> 16:46.070
<i>You</i> happened, you jackass.

16:46.171 --> 16:48.605
<i>Turns out that raisin'the money</i>
<i>to pay back the loan shark...</i>

16:48.707 --> 16:51.574
<i>had hitJoy and her friends</i>
<i>harder than I expected.</i>

16:51.677 --> 16:53.577
<i>Since the lawyer's checks bounced...</i>

16:53.679 --> 16:55.840
<i>Tammy had no way</i>
<i>to pay the loan shark.</i>

16:55.948 --> 16:58.473
I'm sorry he took
your plumbing truck, baby.

16:58.584 --> 17:01.075
We'll be okay.
What's the worst that could happen?

17:01.186 --> 17:04.451
- [Explosion]
- <i>Answer? A busted water heater.</i>

17:06.358 --> 17:09.350
We probably should've kept
a couple of wrenches.

17:10.996 --> 17:12.930
<i>Sylvia gave the loan shark</i>
<i>her furnace...</i>

17:13.032 --> 17:14.932
<i>and had to find other ways</i>
<i>to keep warm.</i>

17:15.034 --> 17:19.198
Hey, that's better.
Move over.

17:25.477 --> 17:28.446
<i>And Joy had to hand over</i>
<i>all her appliances.</i>

17:28.547 --> 17:31.846
What do you want me to say, Darnell?
It looked like a sound investment.

17:31.950 --> 17:36.717
Besides, joke's gonna be on him when
he finds out that crisper don't work for squat.

17:36.822 --> 17:39.791
<i>OnceJoy and Darnell</i>
<i>lost their refrigerator...</i>

17:39.892 --> 17:44.090
<i>Christmas came early for all</i>
<i>the neighborhood flies-all 10,000 of'em.</i>

17:46.632 --> 17:48.600
<i>Without money for an exterminator...</i>

17:48.700 --> 17:51.328
<i>the Turners had no choice</i>
<i>but to move outside.</i>

17:54.306 --> 17:58.174
So, did you come here to gloat? Or is it
just natural that, after flies, maggots show up?

17:58.277 --> 18:01.735
Excuse me.
How much would it cost...

18:01.847 --> 18:05.510
to hire an exterminator to-
to get rid of all these flies?

18:05.617 --> 18:08.415
- I don't know. Couple hundred bucks?
- [Check Tears]

18:11.523 --> 18:13.423
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What are you doin'?

18:13.525 --> 18:15.322
Excuse me, miss.

18:15.427 --> 18:18.021
Could you use a donation
to help with your flood damage?

18:18.130 --> 18:20.462
Is this some kinda scam?
'Cause if it is...

18:20.566 --> 18:23.558
it's someone else's turn
to have sex with the gross guy.

18:23.669 --> 18:27.002
Don't give me that look, Don.
We already talked about this.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.801
Okay, stop.

18:28.907 --> 18:31.637
I put a lot of effort into gettin' this money
out of these people.

18:31.743 --> 18:33.768
How can you just give it back?

18:33.879 --> 18:36.507
Come on. Laugh at 'em.
They're fools.

18:36.615 --> 18:40.346
Earl, I don't have that much
goin' on in my life.

18:40.452 --> 18:42.352
I mean, I'm a rodeo fan...

18:42.454 --> 18:46.447
and I do like to whittle,
but not that much.

18:46.558 --> 18:48.526
But when I gave to those charities-

18:48.627 --> 18:50.891
even though they weren't real-

18:50.996 --> 18:52.896
I thought I was helpin' people.

18:52.998 --> 18:55.990
And that made me feel good.

18:56.101 --> 18:58.865
Looks to me like these people
really have been through...

18:58.971 --> 19:01.235
some floods and fires and such.

19:01.340 --> 19:04.468
This is a chance for me
to help people for real.

19:04.576 --> 19:06.976
I really think
you're missin' the point.

19:07.079 --> 19:09.343
These are the exact people
who've been rippin' you off.

19:09.448 --> 19:11.916
I know.

19:21.527 --> 19:24.519
[Gasps, Crying]

19:27.099 --> 19:30.796
- [Bell Ringing]
- <i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>I was amazed by Mr. Hill's generosity.</i>

19:30.903 --> 19:33.770
<i>And it definitely had an effect</i>
<i>on the people he helped.</i>

19:33.872 --> 19:37.364
<i>When you've been a jerk and someone's</i>
<i>still nice to you, it's a powerful thing.</i>

19:37.476 --> 19:40.172
<i>#Vixen and Blitzen and all his reindeer#</i>

19:40.279 --> 19:42.179
- <i># Pullin'on the reins #</i>
- Ho, ho, ho.

19:42.281 --> 19:44.306
<i>#Bells are ringin</i>; <i>children singin'#</i>

19:44.416 --> 19:46.543
<i>#All is merry and bright #</i>

19:46.652 --> 19:50.418
<i>Seein'what Mr. Hill had done</i>
<i>really put me in the Christmas spirit.</i>

19:50.522 --> 19:53.514
<i>Wakey, wakey,</i>
<i>Christmas snowflakies.</i>

19:53.625 --> 19:56.685
<i>#Here comes Santa Claus</i>
<i>right down Santa Claus Lane #</i>

19:56.795 --> 19:58.922
<i>#He's got a bag</i>
<i>that's filled with toys #</i>

19:59.031 --> 20:02.296
- <i># For boys and girls again #</i>
- Thanks, Earl.

